I am currently a second-year Computer Engineering and Computer Science major at Northeastern University. I enjoy coding and have a passion for robotics and programming. I can often be found working on an array of technical projects. I have created websites, apps, and prototypes for startup ideas, databases, robots, boats, and more. I love being able to use creativity and innovation to transforming ideas into physical products. The more I learn about the field through my projects I have come to realize how I can use creativity and innovation to better my community. The idea of being able to help those around me while following my passions is what drives me to study Computer Engineering and Computer Science. At Northeastern I am a part of an array of organizations and clubs and enjoy being actively involved in the community . Outside of coding, I enjoy traveling, running, playing instruments, and hammocking
